From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0045/N] TimeZone_md.c: bsd target uses linux/macosx code path

`src/java.base/unix/native/libjava/TimeZone_md.c` provides two
implementations of `getPlatformTimeZoneID()`:

  #if defined(__linux__) || defined(MACOSX)
    static char *getPlatformTimeZoneID() { ... readlink-based ... }
  #elif defined(_AIX)
    static char *getPlatformTimeZoneID() { ... }
  #endif

On bsd target, neither branch matches, so `getPlatformTimeZoneID`
is never defined — yet `findJavaTZ_md()` at line 484 still calls
it (causing implicit-function-declaration errors).

FreeBSD/CheriBSD uses `/etc/localtime` as a symlink into
`/usr/share/zoneinfo`, exactly matching the macOS layout. The
existing linux/macosx code path (which reads the symlink target
to derive the Olson tzid) works for BSD without modification.

Add `_ALLBSD_SOURCE` to the outer guard so bsd gets the same
implementation.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0045)

--- a/src/java.base/unix/native/libjava/TimeZone_md.c
+++ b/src/java.base/unix/native/libjava/TimeZone_md.c
@@ -75,7 +75,7 @@
 static const char *ETC_ENVIRONMENT_FILE = "/etc/environment";
 #endif

-#if defined(__linux__) || defined(MACOSX)
+#if defined(__linux__) || defined(MACOSX) || defined(_ALLBSD_SOURCE)

 /*
  * Returns a pointer to the zone ID portion of the given zoneinfo file
